		<h2 class='diff-currentversion-title'>Revision as of 01:14, 29 November 2014</h2>
<div class="hatnote relarticle mainarticle">Main article: <a href="/wiki/History_of_the_Halifax_Regional_Municipality" title="History of the Halifax Regional Municipality" class="mw-redirect">History of the Halifax Regional Municipality</a></div>
<p><b>Dartmouth</b> founded in 1750, is a Metropolitan Area and former city in the <a href="/wiki/Canadian_province" title="Canadian province" class="mw-redirect">Canadian province</a> of <a href="/wiki/Nova_Scotia" title="Nova Scotia">Nova Scotia</a>.</p>
<p>Dartmouth and the neighbouring metropolitan area of <a href="/wiki/City_of_Halifax" title="City of Halifax" class="mw-redirect">Halifax</a> form the urban core of the <a href="/wiki/Halifax_Regional_Municipality,_Nova_Scotia" title="Halifax Regional Municipality, Nova Scotia" class="mw-redirect">Halifax Regional Municipality</a> (HRM). Both cities, along with the town of <a href="/wiki/Bedford,_Nova_Scotia" title="Bedford, Nova Scotia">Bedford</a> and the Municipality of the County of Halifax were dissolved on April 1, 1996 when they were amalgamated into HRM.</p>
<p></p>
